For this project, I expanded the ultrasonic distance sensor system by mounting the HC-SR04 sensor onto an MG996R servo motor to scan across a range of angles. The servo sweeps from -45 degrees to +45 degrees in 5-degree steps while measuring distance at each position and displaying the range on a four-digit seven-segment display.

I implemented the project using bare-metal CMSIS and PlatformIO, using timers and interrupts to control servo positioning, measure ultrasonic echo pulse widths, update the SSD display, and transmit angle, pulse width, and range data through USART at 115200 baud. This project gave me experience with PWM servo control, ultrasonic sensing, timer-based measurement, UART communication, display multiplexing, and real-time embedded system integration.
